{"word":"εὐπειθής","slug":"εὐπειθής","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>εὐπειθής</b></el> <el>(εὐ-πειθής, ές) </el><br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><a href='S:πείθω'><el>πείθω</el></a>\n<p/><div class='li500'><b>I. </b><i>ready to obey, obedient</i>, <el>τινι</el> <b><a href='S:Aeschylus'>Aesch.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Plato'>Plat.</a></b>; also <el>τινος</el>, <b><a href='S:Plato'>Plat.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>II. </b><a href='S:active signification'><a href='S:Active voice'>act.</a></a> <i>persuasive</i>, <b><a href='S:Aeschylus'>Aesch.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}